From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ROCKNIX <noreply@rocknix.org>
Date: Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: rockchip: rk3576: Add DesignWare DisplayPort controller node

Add the DP controller node at 0x27e40000 to the RK3576 base DTSI.
The controller uses the USBDP combo PHY for USB-C DisplayPort Alt Mode.
Enabling this allows boards to route VOP2 VP2 output through the DP
controller to the USB-C port for external display output.

Clock mapping (RK3576 mainline CRU):
  apb  -> PCLK_DP0         (APB bus clock)
  aux  -> CLK_AUX16MHZ_0   (16 MHz AUX channel clock)
  hdcp -> ACLK_DP0          (AXI clock)

Verified against ANBERNIC RG Vita Pro BSP device tree:
  address 0x27e40000, interrupt SPI 337 level-high,
  power domain VO1, reset SRST_DP0.

A port@2 endpoint is added to the DP node's ports block so the DRM
bridge audio framework (DRM_BRIDGE_OP_DP_AUDIO) can discover SAI7 as
the CPU DAI via hdmi_audio_dai_port=2.  The matching endpoint is added
to the SAI7 node to complete the OF graph.  SAI7 (0x27ed0000) shares
the VO1 power domain with the DP controller and acts as I2S master
delivering audio samples to the DP controller's audio sampler hardware.

Signed-off-by: ROCKNIX <noreply@rocknix.org>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi | 45 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 45 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
@@ -1482,6 +1482,45 @@
 				};
 			};
 		};
+		dp: dp@27e40000 {
+			compatible = "rockchip,rk3576-dp";
+			reg = <0x0 0x27e40000 0x0 0x30000>;
+			interrupts = <GIC_SPI 337 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
+			assigned-clocks = <&cru CLK_AUX16MHZ_0>;
+			assigned-clock-rates = <16000000>;
+			clocks = <&cru PCLK_DP0>, <&cru CLK_AUX16MHZ_0>,
+				 <&cru ACLK_DP0>;
+			clock-names = "apb", "aux", "hdcp";
+			phys = <&usbdp_phy PHY_TYPE_DP>;
+			power-domains = <&power RK3576_PD_VO1>;
+			resets = <&cru SRST_DP0>;
+			#sound-dai-cells = <0>;
+			status = "disabled";
+
+			ports {
+				#address-cells = <1>;
+				#size-cells = <0>;
+
+				dp0_in: port@0 {
+					#address-cells = <1>;
+					#size-cells = <0>;
+					reg = <0>;
+				};
+
+				dp0_out: port@1 {
+					#address-cells = <1>;
+					#size-cells = <0>;
+					reg = <1>;
+				};
+
+				dp0_sound_in: port@2 {
+					reg = <2>;
+					dp0_i2s_in: endpoint {
+						remote-endpoint = <&sai7_dp_out>;
+					};
+				};
+			};
+		};

 		sai7: sai@27ed0000 {
 			compatible = "rockchip,rk3576-sai";
@@ -1499,6 +1538,12 @@
 			#sound-dai-cells = <0>;
 			sound-name-prefix = "SAI7";
 			status = "disabled";
+
+			port {
+				sai7_dp_out: endpoint {
+					remote-endpoint = <&dp0_i2s_in>;
+				};
+			};
 		};

 		sai8: sai@27ee0000 {
